PURE FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING HAS A SET OF
RULES TO FOLLOW


1.No state - should not depends upon a outside variable , which is not defined in the scope of that function

2.Pure Functions - function should not depends upon  global variable

3. No Side Effects : Function have no side effect other than everything inside of the body of your function

4.Higher Order Functions
  *The function takes one or more functions as parameters.
  *The function returns another function as a result.
